￼￼￼Secondhand Swagger is more than a name; it's a lifestyle. We're an Atlanta-based band with a passion for vintage sounds and style, disciples of soul music from the 1960s and 70s. Our mission is to keep this music alive and people dancing, taking it back to a time when lyrics and melodies came from the heart with a wink and a laugh. 

Secondhand Swagger was just a dream when Abby Wren (vocals) and Scott Bryan (drums and vocals) got together in 2008, spending every Sunday for a year in a song-writing sojourn. Secondhand grew member by member and the family no includes Tiffany White (keys, vocals), Rob Lane (guitar, vocals) and Jairaj Swann (bass, hot peppers).

We believe we're soulmates brought together to keep this vintage sound alive.
